<item>
            <title>[SPARK-21327] ArrayConstructor should handle an array of typecode &apos;l&apos; as long rather than int in Python 2.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-21327</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently &lt;tt&gt;ArrayConstructor&lt;/tt&gt; handles an array of typecode &lt;tt&gt;&apos;l&apos;&lt;/tt&gt; as &lt;tt&gt;int&lt;/tt&gt; when converting Python object in Python 2 into Java object, so if the value is larger than &lt;tt&gt;Integer.MAX_VALUE&lt;/tt&gt; or smaller than &lt;tt&gt;Integer.MIN_VALUE&lt;/tt&gt; then the overflow occurs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; array
data = [Row(l=array.array(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;l&apos;&lt;/span&gt;, [-9223372036854775808, 0, 9223372036854775807]))]
df = spark.createDataFrame(data)
df.show(truncate=False)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;+----------+
|l         |
+----------+
|[0, 0, -1]|
+----------+
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This should be:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;+----------------------------------------------+
|l                                             |
+----------------------------------------------+
|[-9223372036854775808, 0, 9223372036854775807]|
+----------------------------------------------+
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
